<subSubSection id="312C4E607841AC3A66AA12EBA2B4C0EA" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="551DD78A36D7BA72F27F4C4B9EADDC6B" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AF05562DF8538970AFEDA7862E0D02BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
Members of 
<taxonomicName id="C0DF5407B4537AC0D3140A4CA97D43DC" baseAuthorityName="Mao" baseAuthorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Retusigaster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Retusigaster brevitarsis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevitarsis">
<emphasis id="79E21665F0A06AAFB6BA068F898917AF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Retusigaster brevitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="208823BA413C185FBD44F0343D55BB9B" class="Insecta" genus="R." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="R. rubidus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubidus">
<emphasis id="F97BC837B77B73A1F69DA1A51A8A0CC0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">R. rubidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="AF31F7310B86D0F1F798D422408E972D" baseAuthorityName="Mao" baseAuthorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Retusigaster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Retusigaster brevitarsis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevitarsis">
<emphasis id="830D8DCE28CC6EE8A68FF7A6AC90A00C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Retusigaster brevitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other members of the genus by the following characters: body length (~ 7.0mm); notauli smooth (Key image 3A); mesoscutum mostly orange pale; forewing entirely infuscate with dark (Key image 5B); metasoma mostly orange pale.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
